<paragraph id="A10836F4FFC01D6836A1FF462124F5F0" blockId="23.[144,281,167,191]" box="[144,281,167,191]" pageId="23" pageNumber="1424">
<emphasis id="93C3EAE6FFC01D6836A1FF462124F5F0" box="[144,281,167,191]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="1424">Morphology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A10836F4FFC01D6836A1FF2F2154F4CA" blockId="23.[144,1101,206,389]" pageId="23" pageNumber="1424">
As described by 
<bibRefCitation id="C5264B05FFC01D683765FF2E2266F5A9" author="van Achterberg C" box="[340,603,206,230]" pageId="23" pageNumber="1424" pagination="1 - 102" refId="ref25789" refString="van Achterberg C. 1991. Revision of the genera of the Afrotropical and W. Palearctic Rogadinae Foerster (Hymenoptera: Braconidae). Zool Verh Leiden. 273: 1 - 102." type="journal article" year="1991">van Achterberg (1991)</bibRefCitation>
. In addition, frons without carina in front of anterior ocellus, but with carinate ridge along edge next to and almost touching eye. Fore wing vein m-cu forming angle of approximately 110 
<superScript id="56C29BBCFFC01D683547FEEB2342F454" attach="left" box="[886,895,266,283]" fontSize="7" pageId="23" pageNumber="1424">◦</superScript>
with 3-CU1; vein 2-M 2.5 times length of r-m. Hind wing basal and subbasal cells and basal part of discal+subdiscal cell largely setose, though setosity somewhat less dense than on rest of wing membrane.
</paragraph>
